This paper deals with distributed optimization over wireless networks, which involves information theory (cs.IT) and network infrastructure (cs.NI). The use of learning algorithms suggests a focus on machine learning (cs.LG) and control systems (cs.SY). Finally, the optimization techniques used in the paper may also fall under the category of mathematical optimization (cs.MA).
